children.subject: There is always a cap on the waitlist size for every lecture / section. And yes, that is what the error means: that one of these has a full waitlist.
I just checked the lab and discussion sessions and they're both open: 22 and 11 open seats respectively. Could it be that these are reserved?
Wait I just tried again after changing nothing and it worked, maybe the system was acting weird? Thanks for the help guys!
For future, yes, seats are definitely reserved. Please review our website and/or pinned posts for this information
I am not certain but I believe that means that there is a cap on the waitlist size for either lecture, lab, or section and the waitlist is full.

history.content:
Make sure the lab/discussion's waitlist is not full.

The discussion/lab section being open (the green light on CalCentral) hides this fact, but if you manually check*, the waitlist for the discussion could be full. It is possible for a section to be shown as open while the waitlist is completely full..

*you can check by clicking on the respective section's number on the left side of the page on http://classes.berkeley.edu/content/2018-spring-eleng-16a-001-lec-001.
